narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Spanish 309 is a really good class. It can be a little dry at times, but the time period in spanish history is fascinating and most of the literature is really good. Definitely a harder spanish class. Be prepared to read long spanish novels from the 1800s and to write a lot and research in spanish. It's the same workload you would have in other literature classes but in a different language. Definitely worth taking though, especially if you are interested in the history of Spain or Spanish literature.
Yes I would recommend it. Lots of reading but interesting and a good professor.

Spanish 309 is definitely a course with a heavy workload. If you are good at reading Spanish, then I highly recommend the class. It is reading-intensive but all the material chosen is very interesting. I would recommend to all students to take advantage of office hours. Office hours are a great way to get feedback on your writing assignments, come up with new ideas or just practice speaking. I wish I had gone there from the beginning of the semester.
Small discussion class, easy reading that is interesting, cool teacher and only a few papers that were easy.
Great class. Would absolutely recommend it to anyone looking to continue their Spanish study and interested in the material.
